name: JPEG 2000 Code Stream File
summary: A JPC file is a bitmap image saved in the JPEG 2000 Code Stream format, a variation of the standard JPEG format. It contains image data compressed with JPEG 2000 advanced wavelet compression. The format supports color depths of 8, 24, and 32 bits per pixel and grayscale, RGB, YCbCr, XYZ, and Lab color spaces.
